It is a secondary neuron of the 07B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It sends output to the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 11 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
